.TH "of_find_node_opts_by_path" 9 "of_find_node_opts_by_path" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
of_find_node_opts_by_path \- Find a node matching a full OF path
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct device_node *" of_find_node_opts_by_path
.BI "(const char *path "  ","
.BI "const char **opts "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "path" 12
Either the full path to match, or if the path does not
start with '/', the name of a property of the /aliases
node (an alias).  In the case of an alias, the node
matching the alias' value will be returned.
.IP "opts" 12
Address of a pointer into which to store the start of
an options string appended to the end of the path with
a ':' separator.

Valid paths:
/foo/bar        Full path
foo             Valid alias
foo/bar         Valid alias + relative path

Returns a node pointer with refcount incremented, use
\fBof_node_put\fP on it when done.
